<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFCF6A70FCF39C7F1C32B668" pageId="52" pageNumber="810" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFCF6A70FCF39C7F1C32B668" blockId="52.[782,1376,2523,2946]" lastBlockId="52.[168,1374,2953,3459]" pageId="52" pageNumber="810">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCF6A70FCF39C7F1DC5B175" baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[783,965,2598,2631]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">Hypsugo savii</taxonomicName>
is included within the Eurasian clade closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCF6A70FB519C171D38B1A4" baseAuthorityName="Bobrinskii" baseAuthorityYear="1926" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alaschanicus">H. alaschanicus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCF6A70FCAA9C241DC6B1A4" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1904" box="[854,966,2685,2710]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ariel">H. ariel</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCF6A70FBCC9C241AD3B1A4" authorityName="Harrison" authorityYear="1979" box="[1072,1235,2685,2710]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="arabicus">H. arabicus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCF6A70FB0D9C241DB3B18C" baseAuthorityName="Bobrinskii" baseAuthorityYear="1926" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="alaschanicus">Hypsugo alaschanicus</taxonomicName>
has often been included under 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCF6A70FC8F9C911DE2B1D7" baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[883,994,2760,2789]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">H. savii</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies, but morphological and genetic data support their status as separate species. Specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCF6A70FCF29D601D94B068" box="[782,916,2873,2906]" name="Myanmar" pageId="52" pageNumber="810">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
that were previously included in 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCF6A70FCF29D3C1D7BB0B0" baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[782,891,2917,2946]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">H. savii</taxonomicName>
under the subspecies austenianus are now considered to represent 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCF6A70FD749DD01D3CB098" box="[648,828,2953,2986]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pulveratus">H. pulveratus</taxonomicName>
. There are four highly divergent lineages within 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCF6A70FEAD9DE91FBAB0E3" baseAuthorityName="Bonaparte" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[337,442,2992,3025]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="savii">H. savii</taxonomicName>
that may ultimately represent distinct species; the Moroccan lineage, south-west European lineage (south 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCF6A70FD069D811D4CB0CB" box="[762,844,3032,3065]" name="Georgia" pageId="52" pageNumber="810">Iberia</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCF6A70FC7C9D811A28B0CB" box="[896,1064,3032,3065]" name="Switzerland" pageId="52" pageNumber="810">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
), Levant lineage, and south-east European and Anatolian lineage (along with some specimens in 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCF6A70FB079DA61B4DB712" box="[1275,1357,3071,3104]" name="Israel" pageId="52" pageNumber="810">Israel</collectingCountry>
). Specimens from the Caucasus to 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFCF6A70FD699A731CDEB775" box="[661,734,3114,3143]" name="India" pageId="52" pageNumber="810">India</collectingCountry>
have not yet been compared genetically to other populations and further studies are needed. Four subspecies are tentatively recognized, and the name austenianus (from 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFFCF6A70FD0B9A2C1D8EB7A4" box="[759,910,3189,3222]" country="India" name="Meghalaya" pageId="52" pageNumber="810">Meghalaya</collectingRegion>
) is only tentatively recognized as a subspecies, although it may represent this species, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFCF6A70FC799AC41A36B78C" box="[901,1078,3229,3262]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Hypsugo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="52" pageNumber="810" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pulveratus">H. pulveratus</taxonomicName>
, or a distinct species. The subspecific name ochromixtus is replaced with the name darwini, which has priority since it is the older name available for that lineage; it has been suggested that this taxon represents a distinct species (referred to as H. cf. darwini in recent studies). Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
